{"title_page": "Navigator Records", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{infobox record label\n| image = [[File:Navigator_Records_logo.png]]\n| parent = \n| founded = 2008\n| founder = \n| distributor = [[Proper Music Distribution]]\n| genre = [[folk music|Folk]] and roots music. \n| country = United Kingdom\n| location      = \n| url = {{unbulleted list|[http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/ Navigator Records]}}\n}}\n\n'''Navigator Records''' is a small [[independent record label]] in the United Kingdom, specialising in [[folk music|folk]] and roots music. It is wholly owned by [[Proper Music Distribution]]<ref name= \"DueDil\">{{cite web | url=https://www.duedil.com/company/06394939/navigator-records-limited/people | title=Navigator Records Limited|publisher= DueDil|accessdate =25 April 2014}}</ref> and was launched in 2008.\n\nMusicians who have recorded on Navigator Records include  [[Alyth (singer)|Alyth]],<ref name=\"List\">{{cite magazine | url=http://www.list.co.uk/articles/navigator-records/ | title=Aylth \u2013 People Like Me |magazine=[[The List (magazine)|The List]] | date=2 April 2009 | accessdate=30 June 2013}}</ref> [[Jon Boden]],<ref name=\"Boden\">{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/jon-boden/ | title=Jon Boden | publisher=Navigator Records | accessdate=10 April 2013}}</ref> [[Bellowhead]],<ref name=\"Green\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/worldfolkandjazz/9725048/Bellowhead-interview-Rebooting-folk-for-the-Top-20-or-for-a-packed-pub-at-2am.html | title=Bellowhead interview: Rebooting folk for the Top 20 \u2013 or for a packed pub at 2am | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=6 December 2012 | accessdate=27 March 2013 | author=Green, Thomas H | location=London}}</ref> [[Bella Hardy]],<ref name=\"Coleman\">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-bella-hardy-songs-lost-amp-stolen-navigator-2269156.html | title=Album: Bella Hardy, Songs Lost & Stolen (Navigator) | work=[[The Independent]] | date=17 April 2011 | accessdate=25 April 2014 | author=[[Nick Coleman (British writer)|Coleman, Nick]] | location=London}}</ref> [[Boo Hewerdine]],<ref name=\"Fish\">{{cite web | url=http://www.fishrecords.co.uk/artists/godblesstheprettythings.html | title=Boo Hewerdine: God Bless the Pretty Things | publisher=Fish Records | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref> [[Sean Lakeman]],<ref name=\"Gill\">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-kathryn-roberts--sean-lakeman-hidden-people-navigator-7917503.html | title=Album: Kathryn Roberts & Sean Lakeman, Hidden People (Navigator) | work=[[The Independent]] | date=7 July 2012 | accessdate=9 April 2013 | author=Gill, Andy | location=London}}</ref>  [[Lau (band)|Lau]],<ref name=\"Lau\">{{cite web | url=http://www.worldmusic.co.uk/lau_arc_light | title=Lau \u2013 \"Arc Light\" | publisher=Worldmusic.co.uk | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref> [[Merrymouth (band)|Merrymouth]],<ref name=\"Merrymouth\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/3848332-Merrymouth |title=Merrymouth |website=[[Discogs]] |access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> [[Paper Aeroplanes]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/paper-aeroplanes/ | title=Paper Aeroplanes \u2013 Little Letters Countdown | publisher=Navigator Records | date=7 May 2013 | accessdate=22 May 2013}}</ref>\n[[Kathryn Roberts]] and [[Lucy Ward (musician)|Lucy Ward]].<ref name=\"Artists\">{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/ | title=Artists | publisher=Navigator Records | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/  Official website]\n\n[[Category:2008 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:British independent record labels]]\n[[Category:Record labels established in 2008]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}\n{{infobox record label\n| image = [[File:Navigator_Records_logo.png]]\n| parent = \n| founded = 2008\n| founder = \n| distributor = [[Proper Music Distribution]]\n| genre = [[folk music|Folk]] and roots music. \n| country = United Kingdom\n| location      = \n| url = {{unbulleted list|[http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/ Navigator Records]}}\n}}\n\n'''Navigator Records''' is a small [[independent record label]] in the United Kingdom, specialising in [[folk music|folk]] and roots music. It is wholly owned by [[Proper Music Distribution]]<ref name= \"DueDil\">{{cite web | url=https://www.duedil.com/company/06394939/navigator-records-limited/people | title=Navigator Records Limited|publisher= DueDil|accessdate =25 April 2014}}</ref> and was launched in 2008.\n\nMusicians who have recorded on Navigator Records include  [[Alyth (singer)|Alyth]],<ref name=\"List\">{{cite magazine | url=http://www.list.co.uk/articles/navigator-records/ | title=Aylth \u2013 People Like Me |magazine=[[The List (magazine)|The List]] | date=2 April 2009 | accessdate=30 June 2013}}</ref> [[Jon Boden]],<ref name=\"Boden\">{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/jon-boden/ | title=Jon Boden | publisher=Navigator Records | accessdate=10 April 2013}}</ref> [[Bellowhead]],<ref name=\"Green\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/worldfolkandjazz/9725048/Bellowhead-interview-Rebooting-folk-for-the-Top-20-or-for-a-packed-pub-at-2am.html | title=Bellowhead interview: Rebooting folk for the Top 20 \u2013 or for a packed pub at 2am | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=6 December 2012 | accessdate=27 March 2013 | author=Green, Thomas H | location=London}}</ref> [[Bella Hardy]],<ref name=\"Coleman\">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-bella-hardy-songs-lost-amp-stolen-navigator-2269156.html | title=Album: Bella Hardy, Songs Lost & Stolen (Navigator) | work=[[The Independent]] | date=17 April 2011 | accessdate=25 April 2014 | author=[[Nick Coleman (British writer)|Coleman, Nick]] | location=London}}</ref> [[Boo Hewerdine]],<ref name=\"Fish\">{{cite web | url=http://www.fishrecords.co.uk/artists/godblesstheprettythings.html | title=Boo Hewerdine: God Bless the Pretty Things | publisher=Fish Records | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref> [[Sean Lakeman]],<ref name=\"Gill\">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-kathryn-roberts--sean-lakeman-hidden-people-navigator-7917503.html | title=Album: Kathryn Roberts & Sean Lakeman, Hidden People (Navigator) | work=[[The Independent]] | date=7 July 2012 | accessdate=9 April 2013 | author=Gill, Andy | location=London}}</ref>  [[Lau (band)|Lau]],<ref name=\"Lau\">{{cite web | url=http://www.worldmusic.co.uk/lau_arc_light | title=Lau \u2013 \"Arc Light\" | publisher=Worldmusic.co.uk | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref> [[Merrymouth (band)|Merrymouth]],<ref name=\"Merrymouth\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/3848332-Merrymouth |title=Merrymouth |website=[[Discogs]] |access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> [[Paper Aeroplanes]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/paper-aeroplanes/ | title=Paper Aeroplanes \u2013 Little Letters Countdown | publisher=Navigator Records | date=7 May 2013 | accessdate=22 May 2013}}</ref>\n[[Kathryn Roberts]] and [[Lucy Ward (musician)|Lucy Ward]].<ref name=\"Artists\">{{cite web | url=http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/artists/ | title=Artists | publisher=Navigator Records | accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.navigatorrecords.co.uk/  Official website]\n\n[[Category:British independent record labels]]\n[[Category:Record labels established in 2008]]\n[[Category:2008 establishments in England]]\n", "name_user": "Headhitter", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:Reordered cats", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Navigator_Records"}
{"title_page": "Lu\u00eds Machado", "text_new": "{{short description|Portuguese footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{for|the Portuguese Olympic rower|Lu\u00eds Machado (rower)}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Lu\u00eds Machado\n| image =\n| fullname = Lu\u00eds Miguel Vieira Babo Machado\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|11|4|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Lamego]], Portugal\n| height = {{height|m=1.68}}\n| position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub = [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]]\n| clubnumber = 70\n| youthyears1 = 1999\u20132010 | youthclubs1 = [[U.S.C. Paredes|Paredes]]\n| youthyears2 = 2010\u20132011 | youthclubs2 = [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]]\n| years1 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs1 = [[U.S.C. Paredes|Paredes]] | caps1 = 2 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2011\u20132014 | clubs2 = [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]] | caps2 = 60 | goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2014\u20132015 | clubs3 = [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]] | caps3 = 32 | goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2016\u20132019 | clubs4 = [[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]] | caps4 = 85 | goals4 = 7\n| years5 = 2019\u2013 | clubs5 = [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]] | caps5 = 16 | goals5 = 1\n| club-update = 8 March 2020\n}}\n'''Lu\u00eds Miguel Vieira Babo Machado''' (born 4 November 1992) is a Portuguese [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Moreirense F.C.]] as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Lamego]], [[Viseu District]], Machado joined [[U.S.C. Paredes]] in 1999, aged only six. In 2009, whilst still a junior, he made his senior debut, playing two [[Portuguese Third Division|fourth division]] games with the club.\n\nIn the summer of 2010, Machado signed with [[S.C. Freamunde]], where he completed his development. He was promoted to the first team for the [[2011\u201312 Liga de Honra|2011\u201312 season]], playing his first match in the [[Segunda Liga|second level]] on 25 September 2011, a 0\u20131 away loss against [[C.F. Os Belenenses]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/belenenses-freamunde-1-0-leo-kanu-garante-3-pontos-718782.html|title=Belenenses-Freamunde, 1\u20130: L\u00e9o Kan\u00fa garante 3 pontos|trans-title=Belenenses-Freamunde, 1\u20130: L\u00e9o Kan\u00fa confirms 3 points|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|language=Portuguese|date=25 September 2011|accessdate=7 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 July 2014, Machado agreed to a two-year contract with another division two side, [[C.D. Tondela]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/tondela/detalhe/luis-machado-assina-por-duas-temporadas-892990|title=Lu\u00eds Machado assina por duas temporadas|trans-title=Lu\u00eds Machado signs for two seasons|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=5 July 2014|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> He scored two goals<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/2a-liga/noticias/interior/tondela-surpreendeu-uniao-na-madeira-4455059.html|title=Tondela surpreendeu Uni\u00e3o na Madeira|trans-title=Tondela surprised Uni\u00e3o in Madeira|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|language=Portuguese|date=15 March 2015|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/tondela-chaves-2-2-empate-adia-decisoes-para-a-ultima-jornada-949029|title=Tondela-Chaves, 2\u20132: Empate adia decis\u00f5es para a \u00faltima jornada|trans-title=Tondela-Chaves, 2\u20132: Draw postpones decisions to last round|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=17 May 2015|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> in 26 matches in [[2014\u201315 Segunda Liga|his first year]], as they reached the [[Primeira Liga]] for the first time in 82 years of history.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/freamunde-tondela-1-1-golo-nos-descontos-carimbou-subida-950609|title=Freamunde-Tondela, 1\u20131: Golo nos descontos carimbou subida|trans-title=Freamunde-Tondela, 1\u20131: Injury time goal sealed promotion|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=24 May 2015|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nMachado made his debut in the [[Portuguese football league system|Portuguese top tier]] on 14 August 2015, starting in a 1\u20132 home defeat to [[Sporting CP]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/sporting/interior/penalti-no-final-salvou-sporting-frente-ao-estreante-tondela-4729343.html|title=Pen\u00e1lti no final salvou Sporting frente ao estreante Tondela|trans-title=Late penalty saved Sporting against newcomers Tondela|newspaper=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|first=Jo\u00e3o|last=Ruela|language=Portuguese|date=14 August 2015|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> In the following [[transfer window]], however, he returned to the second division after joining [[C.D. Feirense]] on a short-term deal;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdfeirense.pt/site/2016/01/06/luis-machado-e-o-novo-reforco-do-clube-desportivo-feirense/|title=Lu\u00eds Machado, \u00e9 o novo refor\u00e7o do Clube Desportivo Feirense|trans-title=Lu\u00eds Machado, a new Clube Desportivo Feirense addition|publisher=C.D. Feirense|language=Portuguese|date=6 January 2016|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> after [[2015\u201316 LigaPro|achieving promotion]] and renewing his contract,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdfeirense.pt/site/2016/06/23/luis-machado-renova-contrato/|title=Luis Machado renova contrato!|trans-title=Luis Machado renews contract!|publisher=C.D. Feirense|language=Portuguese|date=23 June 2016|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> he went on to spend a further three seasons with the team, being relegated at the end of [[2018\u201319 Primeira Liga|2018\u201319]] and subsequently released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/mercado/transferencias/edinho-e-luis-machado-despedem-se-do-feirense|title=Edinho e Lu\u00eds Machado despedem-se do Feirense|trans-title=Edinho and Lu\u00eds Machado say goodbye to Feirense|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|date=20 May 2019|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2019 off-season, Machado signed a three-year contract with [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guimaraesdigital.com/index.php/informacao/desporto/55132-luis-machado-o-moreirense-e-um-clube-estavel-na-1-liga|title=Lu\u00eds Machado: \"O Moreirense \u00e9 um clube est\u00e1vel na 1.\u00aa Liga\"|trans-title=Lu\u00eds Machado: \"Moreirense is a stable club in the 1st League\"|publisher=Guimar\u00e3es Digital|language=Portuguese|date=1 July 2019|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ForaDeJogo}}\n*{{Soccerway|luis-miguel-vieira-babo-machado/199131}}\n\n{{Moreirense F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Machado, Luis}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lamego]]\n[[Category:Portuguese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:LigaPro players]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Second Division players]]\n[[Category:S.C. Freamunde players]]\n[[Category:C.D. Tondela players]]\n[[Category:C.D. Feirense players]]\n[[Category:Moreirense F.C. players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Portuguese footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{for|the Portuguese Olympic rower|Lu\u00eds Machado (rower)}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Lu\u00eds Machado\n| image =\n| fullname = Lu\u00eds Miguel Vieira Babo Machado\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|11|4|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Lamego]], Portugal\n| height = {{height|m=1.68}}\n| position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub = [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]]\n| clubnumber = 70\n| youthyears1 = 1999\u20132010 | youthclubs1 = [[U.S.C. Paredes|Paredes]]\n| youthyears2 = 2010\u20132011 | youthclubs2 = [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]]\n| years1 = 2009\u20132010 | clubs1 = [[U.S.C. Paredes|Paredes]] | caps1 = 2 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2011\u20132014 | clubs2 = [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]] | caps2 = 60 | goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2014\u20132015 | clubs3 = [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]] | caps3 = 32 | goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2016\u20132019 | clubs4 = [[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]] | caps4 = 85 | goals4 = 7\n| years5 = 2019\u2013 | clubs5 = [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]] | caps5 = 16 | goals5 = 1\n| club-update = 8 March 2020\n}}\n'''Lu\u00eds Miguel Vieira Babo Machado''' (born 4 November 1992) is a Portuguese [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Moreirense F.C.]] as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Lamego]], [[Viseu District]], Machado joined [[U.S.C. Paredes]] in 1999, aged only six. In 2009, whilst still a junior, he made his senior debut, playing two [[Portuguese Third Division|fourth division]] games with the club.\n\nIn the summer of 2010, Machado signed with [[S.C. Freamunde]], where he completed his development. He was promoted to the first team for the [[2011\u201312 Liga de Honra|2011\u201312 season]], playing his first match in the [[Segunda Liga|second level]] on 25 September 2011, a 0\u20131 away loss against [[C.F. Os Belenenses]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/belenenses-freamunde-1-0-leo-kanu-garante-3-pontos-718782.html|title=Belenenses-Freamunde, 1\u20130: L\u00e9o Kan\u00fa garante 3 pontos|trans-title=Belenenses-Freamunde, 1\u20130: L\u00e9o Kan\u00fa confirms 3 points|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|language=Portuguese|date=25 September 2011|accessdate=7 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 July 2014, Machado agreed to a two-year contract with another division two side, [[C.D. Tondela]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/tondela/detalhe/luis-machado-assina-por-duas-temporadas-892990|title=Lu\u00eds Machado assina por duas temporadas|trans-title=Lu\u00eds Machado signs for two seasons|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=5 July 2014|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> He scored two goals<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/2a-liga/noticias/interior/tondela-surpreendeu-uniao-na-madeira-4455059.html|title=Tondela surpreendeu Uni\u00e3o na Madeira|trans-title=Tondela surprised Uni\u00e3o in Madeira|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|language=Portuguese|date=15 March 2015|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/tondela-chaves-2-2-empate-adia-decisoes-para-a-ultima-jornada-949029|title=Tondela-Chaves, 2\u20132: Empate adia decis\u00f5es para a \u00faltima jornada|trans-title=Tondela-Chaves, 2\u20132: Draw postpones decisions to last round|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=17 May 2015|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> in 26 matches in [[2014\u201315 Segunda Liga|his first year]], as they reached the [[Primeira Liga]] for the first time in 82 years of history.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/freamunde-tondela-1-1-golo-nos-descontos-carimbou-subida-950609|title=Freamunde-Tondela, 1\u20131: Golo nos descontos carimbou subida|trans-title=Freamunde-Tondela, 1\u20131: Injury time goal sealed promotion|newspaper=Record|language=Portuguese|date=24 May 2015|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nMachado made his debut in the [[Portuguese football league system|Portuguese top tier]] on 14 August 2015, starting in a 1\u20132 home defeat to [[Sporting CP]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/sporting/interior/penalti-no-final-salvou-sporting-frente-ao-estreante-tondela-4729343.html|title=Pen\u00e1lti no final salvou Sporting frente ao estreante Tondela|trans-title=Late penalty saved Sporting against newcomers Tondela|newspaper=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|first=Jo\u00e3o|last=Ruela|language=Portuguese|date=14 August 2015|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> In the following [[transfer window]], however, he returned to the second division after joining [[C.D. Feirense]] on a short-term deal;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdfeirense.pt/site/2016/01/06/luis-machado-e-o-novo-reforco-do-clube-desportivo-feirense/|title=Lu\u00eds Machado, \u00e9 o novo refor\u00e7o do Clube Desportivo Feirense|trans-title=Lu\u00eds Machado, a new Clube Desportivo Feirense addition|publisher=C.D. Feirense|language=Portuguese|date=6 January 2016|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> after [[2015\u201316 LigaPro|achieving promotion]] and renewing his contract,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdfeirense.pt/site/2016/06/23/luis-machado-renova-contrato/|title=Luis Machado renova contrato!|trans-title=Luis Machado renews contract!|publisher=C.D. Feirense|language=Portuguese|date=23 June 2016|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref> he went on to spend a further three seasons with the team, being relegated at the end of [[2018\u201319 Primeira Liga|2018\u201319]] and being subsequently released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/mercado/transferencias/edinho-e-luis-machado-despedem-se-do-feirense|title=Edinho e Lu\u00eds Machado despedem-se do Feirense|trans-title=Edinho and Lu\u00eds Machado say goodbye to Feirense|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|date=20 May 2019|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2019 off-season, Machado signed a three-year contract with [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guimaraesdigital.com/index.php/informacao/desporto/55132-luis-machado-o-moreirense-e-um-clube-estavel-na-1-liga|title=Lu\u00eds Machado: \"O Moreirense \u00e9 um clube est\u00e1vel na 1.\u00aa Liga\"|trans-title=Lu\u00eds Machado: \"Moreirense is a stable club in the 1st League\"|publisher=Guimar\u00e3es Digital|language=Portuguese|date=1 July 2019|accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ForaDeJogo}}\n*{{Soccerway|luis-miguel-vieira-babo-machado/199131}}\n\n{{Moreirense F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Machado, Luis}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lamego]]\n[[Category:Portuguese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n